03/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The elimination of al-Qaeda leader Osama bin Laden was welcomed in Kosovo with institutions issuing statements of support Monday (May 2nd). 
The government described it as a turning point in the fight against terrorism, for all people around the world who love freedom and peace. 
Therefore, the government congratulates the US forces on their successful operation. 
"Justice has been served. 
Good has prevailed over evil," President Atifete Jahjaga said. 
(Kohavision, KLAN Kosova, RTK - 02/05/11)
